docs(instructions): update setup guides to use pnpm over npm
- Update the project setup instructions to use pnpm instead of npm, provide additional Linux dependency installation steps, refine directory structure descriptions, and format commands and configuration blocks for clarity. - The instruction for installing Vue I18n has been changed from using npm to pnpm. - Replaced the detailed task instructions with links to separate instruction files for each task, greatly reducing the file's length and centralizing the detailed instructions elsewhere. - Update README instructions to use pnpm instead of npm for installing dependencies, developing, and building the project.
Signed-off-by: CHEN, CHUN <jim60105@gmail.com>

chore(gitignore): add rules for IDE, Node, Rust, and build files
- Add a comprehensive .gitignore file to exclude files and directories related to JetBrains IDEs, Node.js, Yarn, Rust, and various common build, cache, and environment artifacts from version control.

docs: add comprehensive guidelines and copilot instructions set
- Add detailed Copilot instructions outlining coding standards for HTML, JavaScript, and Rust, as well as project-specific guidelines for converting a .NET WinForm project to a Tauri + Rust app using Vue.js, Tailwind CSS, and certain backend libraries, with a note on referencing but not modifying specific code. - Add a comprehensive project initialization instruction file in Traditional Chinese detailing the conversion of a legacy .NET WinForm app to a Tauri + Rust project using Vue.js and Tailwind, requirements for dependency handling, UI design, logging, i18n, error handling, and other project specifications clarified via Q&A format. - Add a new instruction file detailing steps to create a Tauri project with Vue and Tailwind, including tool installation, project setup, framework integration, Tailwind configuration, directory structure, and basic app configuration. - Add instructions in Chinese for building the foundational components of the project, including layout structure, main window, input form elements with validation, and a log display component, all leveraging Pinia store for state management and Tailwind CSS for layout. - Add detailed instructions (in Chinese) for integrating yt-dlp and ffmpeg dependencies, including system checks, download automation, Tauri command interfaces, frontend communication, and required dependencies for Cargo.toml. - Add a detailed task instruction file outlining requirements for implementing YouTube video and clip URL parsing, video information extraction using yt-dlp, time format conversion functions, and relevant regular expressions for parsing YouTube-related information. - Add detailed instructions in Chinese for implementing video downloading and processing core functionalities, including tasks for downloader creation, progress reporting, file naming, segmentation, and temporary file management. - Add detailed instructions (in Chinese) for implementing core UI features, including video URL input and parsing, time range selection, format selection, output directory selection, and download/cancel button functionality, with specific component breakdowns and validation requirements. - Add detailed instructions for implementing real-time UI feedback, including download progress, live log updates, dependency status display, and error message handling features. - Add a new instruction file outlining advanced user experience enhancements, including features like opening the download folder automatically, download notifications, global UI state management using a Pinia store, and real-time input validation with visual feedback. - Add instructions detailing the implementation of user settings, including storing and loading configuration with Tauri Store, remembering output directories and format selections, and persisting detailed logging options. - Add detailed instructions (in Chinese) for setting up a basic i18n infrastructure in a Vue project, including installing Vue I18n, configuring language files, and implementing a language switcher component. - Add instructions for implementing multilingual resources, detailing steps for English and Chinese translations and ensuring that all UI elements support internationalization and localization. - Add instructions in Mandarin for writing Rust backend unit tests, including the use of mocks for network and filesystem operations. - Add instructions for configuring Tauri application packaging, including versioning, update mechanism, icon preparation, metadata, and installer details. - Add Chinese-language instructions detailing the steps to set up CI/CD workflows using GitHub Actions, including build and release automation for both Windows and Linux (Flatpak) targets. - Add a detailed implementation plan in Traditional Chinese for converting the YoutubeSegmentDownloader.NET project to a Tauri + Rust version, outlining project initialization, core backend and frontend development, testing, packaging, internationalization, and deployment steps. - Add a new web design guideline document outlining general design principles, Tailwind CSS usage, HTML best practices, and VanillaJS recommendations, along with a sample component example. - Add the GNU General Public License version 3 (GPLv3) as the project's license. - Add initial README with project overview, features, usage instructions, development setup, and licensing information for the Youtube Segment Downloader in Rust. - Add a new icon file named YoutubeSegmentDownloader.ico to the project.
